&lt;p&gt;The Royal Surrey County Hospital NHS Foundation Trust is recruiting enthusiastic Band 6 Midwives to join their team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for candidates who have the ability to work both in the community setting and in our maternity unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Midwives who are able to meet the challenge of delivering high standards of care and are enthused by both promoting natural birth and delivering the BEST care available to women and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must hold an NMC midwifery registration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to take part in pre interview assessments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Matrons Katy Lucas, Kate Conway or Tanya Ashton for further information or you may wish to arrange an informal visit on 01483 571122 extension 2068, 2160, 4708.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NB, This role may close early if a high volume of applications are received.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
